name: Carol Roberts
text: When they actually play music, they are my favorite oldies station. They play the best music from the best decades. However, they have recently changed their format to three hours of talk in the morning between 9 and noon. They might play half a song each hour, and then they interrupt it. And the talk format seems to primarily be pro-Trump rhetoric. Which makes me wonder who paid them to stop playing music? Updated to say, now that impeachment has happened they are back to music again!

resp.text: Carol this ended last year (2019). In fact, we have a feature now from 950am until 12noon that is called Non Stop Till Noon. It's nothing but music for over two hours. We hope you enjoy that and thanks for listening.

name: Roby Dorsett
text: Don't trust anything you win from 1065 Kiss FM and iHeart Radio.   I won a contest and got a limo ride to Nashville and 4 tickets to a concert. I came and got our swag bag, which we loved.  However, the day before the limo folks called and said it was in the shop, I told them that wasn't acceptable and they needed to get with the radio station to fix it. Instead they showed up with a really old SUV.  It vibrated the whole way there.  Our car would have been better. Concert was great and all, but we were really looking forward to a limo ride, not a ride in a worse SUV than we already own.  I sent an email to the guy that reached out when we won...he never responded. I sent 2 emails actually.  I told the driver that this was not what was agreed...they said we'd work it out.  So, be careful of bait and switch or of just not getting what was promised if you win something or deal with this company.
